<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1437,1251,1781]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">The characters of this genus are as noted above for the tribe and this is regarded as a monophyletic group well supported by morphological and molecular evidence.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1437,1251,1781]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
In this genus 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[347,556,1323,1349]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara (2002b)</bibRefCitation>
proposed six species groups, of which three (
<taxonomicName box="[1062,1162,1323,1349]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fausta">
<emphasis box="[1062,1162,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. fausta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zaddach" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[1176,1357,1323,1349]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibularis">
<emphasis box="[1176,1357,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. mandibularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nemoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. nemoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups) were included in our COI analysis and only one (
<taxonomicName box="[921,1067,1359,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nemoralis">
<emphasis box="[921,1067,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. nemoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group) was included in the NaK analysis. In the COI tree (
<figureCitation box="[439,537,1395,1421]" captionStart="FIGURE 137" captionStartId="226.[151,250,1667,1691]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,188,1636]" captionTargetId="figure-26@226.[151,1436,181,1643]" captionTargetPageId="226" captionText="FIGURE 137. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Neurotoma." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876835" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876835/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Fig. 137</figureCitation>
), the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zaddach" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[598,780,1395,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibularis">
<emphasis box="[598,780,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. mandibularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zaddach" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[869,1051,1395,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibularis">
<emphasis box="[869,1051,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. mandibularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1105,1229,1396,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coreana">
<emphasis box="[1105,1229,1396,1421]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. coreana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) was recovered as monophyletic with 100% UFBoot support, but this clade as well as 
<taxonomicName box="[904,1004,1431,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fausta">
<emphasis box="[904,1004,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. fausta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(representative of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1254,1355,1431,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fausta">
<emphasis box="[1254,1355,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. fausta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group) were within the paraphyletic assemblage of the 
<taxonomicName box="[699,846,1467,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nemoralis">
<emphasis box="[699,846,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. nemoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (five species). Possibly, the 
<taxonomicName box="[1249,1352,1467,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fausta">
<emphasis box="[1249,1352,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. fausta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zaddach" baseAuthorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. mandibularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups may form a group of specialized species within the more generalized, speciose, and heterogeneous 
<taxonomicName box="[224,368,1539,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nemoralis">
<emphasis box="[224,368,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. nemoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1437,1251,1781]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
This genus contains 23 species worldwide, including six species recorded from the Russian Far East and 
<collectingCountry name="South Korea" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">South Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Choi, J. - K. &amp; Lee, J. - W." box="[237,503,1611,1637]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="593 - 599" refId="ref77365" refString="Shinohara, A., Choi, J. - K. &amp; Lee, J. - W. (2018 a) The webspinning sawfly genus Neurotoma (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) of South Korea: Neurotoma silla sp. nov. and a key to species. Zootaxa, 4444 (5), 593 - 599. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4444.5.7" type="journal article" year="2018">
Shinohara 
<emphasis box="[362,421,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
2018a
</bibRefCitation>
). Of the six species, two belong to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zaddach" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[960,1144,1611,1637]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibularis">
<emphasis box="[960,1144,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. mandibularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and four to the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nemoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. nemoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1437,1251,1781]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
The larvae of 
<taxonomicName box="[356,569,1683,1709]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis box="[356,481,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Neurotoma</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
feed on the host leaves, usually gregariously in webs. The known host plants are arborescent 
<taxonomicName box="[330,436,1720,1746]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[453,554,1719,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fausta">
<emphasis box="[453,554,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. fausta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[611,756,1719,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nemoralis">
<emphasis box="[611,756,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. nemoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dumortier" authorityYear="1829" box="[906,1010,1720,1746]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1027,1176,1719,1746]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1027,1121,1720,1746]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Quercus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
) (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1980" box="[1201,1289,1720,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satoi">
<emphasis box="[1201,1289,1720,1745]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. satoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zaddach" baseAuthorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N. mandibularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups).
</paragraph>
